cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a neural network model for analyzing group activity, which involves processing visual data. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The model also involves machine learning techniques, specifically recurrent neural networks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of varying group sizes, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the model on a dataset of volleyball games, which could be considered multimedia (cs.MM).
